Youtube link for tutorial: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Rv6UFGNmNZg

Steps to perform:

1. Create github repository (public)
2. Create a folder and open Vscode
3. Create an environment with below command inside the terminal of vscode:
    "conda create -p venv python==3.8 -y"
4. Activate the env using: conda activate venv/ (Running under cmd and not in powershell)
5. Initialize git repo using: 
    echo "# mlproject" >> README.md
    git init
    git add README.md
    git commit -m "first commit"
    git branch -M main
    git remote add origin https://github.com/jsamanta/mlproject.git
    For first time users need to do git global: 
        https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Customizing-Git-Git-Configuration 
        Verify using : git config --global user.email
        If not set then use below commands
        $ git config --global user.name "John Doe"
        $ git config --global user.email johndoe@example.com
    git push -u origin main
6. Create .gitignore file and select python and commit the changes
7. Create setup.py and requirements.txt files
8. Create src folder an build the package

    
